<SLUG> BC-FBC-UCNOTE-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BRUINS SUFFER LOSSES LONG BEFORE OPENER
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BILLY WITZ  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR; LOS ANGELES _ UCLA, which considered depth one of its strengths
this season, won't be quite as deep when it begins fall practice
today.
</P>
<P>
   Bruins head coach Bob Toledo announced the suspension Friday of
three reserves and also said backup cornerback Julius Williams had
flunked out of school and oft-injured defensive back Lovell Houston
has decided to transfer.
</P>
<P>
   Linebackers Santi Hall and Asi Faoa were suspended for the
season-opener against No. 3-ranked Alabama for violating team
policy, Toledo said.
</P>
<P>
   Faoa is facing a pre-trial hearing Sept. 18 on felony charges of
mayhem and assault for his alleged role in an off-campus fight this
year. The case, in which Faoa has pleaded not guilty, is not
expected to go to trial until after the season. Toledo would not
elaborate on Hall's suspension.
</P>
<P>
   Also suspended was third-string defensive tackle Saia
Makakaufaki, who will miss two games for academic reasons, Toledo
said.
</P>
<P>
   The suspensions of Hall and Faoa could be significant in that it
robs the Bruins of their No. 2 and No. 3 strong-side linebackers
against Alabama. True freshman Brandon Chillar will likely back up
starter Tony White.
</P>
<P>
   Houston, who recently decided to undergo reconstructive surgery
on his right shoulder, decided he wanted to be closer to his family
in Denver while he rehabilitates, Toledo said. Houston's younger
brother Marcus is a running back at the University of Colorado. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
