<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-12 11:07 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A1359 &Cx1f; var-z
u a BC-JEWS-U.S.-REVIEW-2TAK     08-12 0894
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-JEWS-U.S.-REVIEW-2TAKES-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LIEBERMAN NOMINATION REFLECTS ACCEPTANCE OF JEWS IN AMERICAN
MAINSTREAM 
</HEADLINE>
   (The Week in Review)  
 (NOTE TO INTERNATIONAL CLIENTS: For international clients' use by
special arrangement only. Asian and European points: contact Karl
Horwitz in Paris for details and prices (Phone: 47 42 17 11; FAX:
47-42-80-44). Latin American points: contact the Los Angeles office
(Phone: 310-996-0075; FAX: 310-996-0089)  
(editors: optional sidebar at end of article) 
 By LAURIE GOODSTEIN   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   While Ron Wyden was campaigning for a U.S. Senate seat in Oregon
in 1996, a local newspaper ran a letter denouncing him as an
