<P>
   GORE-EXCLUSIVE (Los Angeles) _ Details to come. By Richard L.
Berke.
</P>
<P>
   With photo NYT1
</P>
<P>
   (We plan to move the story by 2 p.m. ET in ``p'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   Top center story:
</P>
<P>
   GORE-BIO-CONGRESS (Washington) _ The Democratic freshman class
that was elected to the House of Representatives in 1976 was a
remarkable one, loaded with bright and ambitious young reformers
who blended the idealism of their generation with the cynicism bred
by Watergate and Vietnam. Many would go on to bigger things _ Dick
Gephardt to the top of the House Democratic leadership, Leon
Panetta to the White House as chief of staff, Barbara Mikulski to
the Senate. But even in this hotbed of ambition, Al Gore stood out.
By Kevin Sack and Robin Toner. (An abridged version is also being
filed.)
</P>
<P>
   With photos NYT6 and NYT7.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 1 p.m. ET in ``p'' news file.)
</P>
