<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-R-GORE-ENVIRONMENT-ART-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GORE INVOKES THE SPIRIT OF AN ENVIRONMENTAL PIONEER 
</HEADLINE>
  (REPEATING to add photo note; no other changes.)  
(ART ADV: Photos NYT13 and 14 are being sent to NYT photo clients.
Nonsubscribers can purchase one-time rights by calling 888-603-1036
or 888-346-9867.) 
 By DAVID BARSTOW   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   SPRINGDALE, Pa. _ If there is an issue in which Vice President
Al Gore feels he has a decided edge over Gov. George W. Bush, it is
the environment.
</P>
<P>
   Gore has written a best-seller on the subject; he has the
