<HEADLINE>
BRIDGE STARS COMPETE FOR CROWN  

</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: Calif., Pa., Fla., Ill.)   c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
  ANAHEIM, Calif. _ Two star-studded teams faced off Saturday in
the final of the Grand National Team Championship at the American
Contract Bridge League's Summer Nationals. The defending champions,
all from Florida, include Michael Seamon, Joseph Shay and three
world champions: Jeff Meckstroth, Eric Rodwell and Robert Levin.
Opposing them is a Californian squad that includes Lew Stansby,
Chip Martel and Peter Weichsel, all world champions; and Rose
Johnson Meltzer, Ron Smith and Kyle Larsen.
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Californian players seemed headed for defeat in the
semifinal Friday night, trailing by 41 IMPs with 16 deals remaining
against a Philadelphia squad. But a 54-IMP stretch effort enabled
them to snatch a 13-IMP victory. In the other semifinal, the
Florida team won comfortably against a Chicago group by 63 IMPs.
