fought through the final hours of a bitter national convention
Saturday, then limped out of town as two parties, each with its own
ideology and nominee. Pat Buchanan, the hard-right columnist and
former Republican presidential contender, took one part. John
Hagelin, a soft-spoken perennial candidate who usually runs under
the banner of the Natural Law Party, took the other. Paul Truax, a
founding member of the Reform Party, took in the results of an
electronic vote Friday at the party's national convention in Long
Beach, Calif. (Monica Almeida/The New York Times)
