to the owners of these houses on Osage Avenue, which were built to
replace those the police destroyed during the Philadelphia MOVE row
house disaster of 1985. The houses, built by a corrupt developer,
have been plagued by construction problems. One of those who
accepted the city's buy-out, John DeVere, owns two houses on Pine
Street and he considers the offer a windfall, since the resale
possibilities had been nil for years. (Richard Perry/The New York
Times)
