   (NYT6) WASHINGTON -- Aug. 12, 2000 -- GORE-BIO-CONGRESS --
Throughout his 16 years in Congress, eight in the House and then
eight in the Senate before becoming Bill Clinton's running mate in
1992, Al Gore was strikingly effective at winning attention by
championing just-over-the-horizon consumer-oriented causes.
Toxic-waste dumping. Genetic testing. Global warming. Gore at a
1989 Senate subcommittee hearing on the effects of global warming.
(Jose R. Lopez/The New York Times)
