Clinton for his success in presiding over the hardy economy but
leave no doubt that ``I'm running on my own agenda, on my own voice
and through my own experiences.'' Gore during a town meeting,
Wednesday in Carthage, Tenn. (Paul Hosefros/The New York Times)
