A9956 &Cx1f; taf-z
u p BC-MRSCLINTON-TEXT-NYT &LR;      08-12 0330
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MRSCLINTON-TEXT-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EXCERPTS FROM MRS. CLINTON'S INTERVIEW 
</HEADLINE>
   c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Following are excerpts from an interview with
Hillary Rodham Clinton at her hotel in Century City on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Q. Is there a danger that what you and President Clinton are
doing here could overshadow Mr. Gore's week here?
</P>
<P>
   A. No. We've talked about it. Everything we're doing has been
coordinated with the vice president and Tipper and top levels of
our staffs. We're doing everything we can to send a very clear
message that if America liked the Clinton-Gore administration, they
will like the Gore-Lieberman administration. And that there is a
continuity here, a commitment to the same issues, a focus on the
New Democratic philosophy.
</P>
<P>
   That's why the convention has been planned the way it is _ where
we came early and we will leave Tuesday morning, and we will join
the Gores and there will be an almost, I don't know how to describe
it exactly, but a kind of passing on, that is, a very explicit
statement by the president about his strong support for and
affection for and admiration for the vice president. And then we're
done. We're gone.
</P>
<P>
   Q. On the race in New York: Why do you think it is that after
everything you've done, in terms of drawing contrasts with your
opponent, you and Mr. Lazio seem to be tied in almost every public
poll?
</P>
<P>
   A. I don't think people have paid a lot of attention to politics
yet. And this is not at all surprising to me. ... If people really
confront the choices that they face, between me and my opponent,
they will know what happens to be true, which is that my stand on
issues and what I will do in the Senate is much more in line with
the majority of New Yorkers. He's the Republican-conservative
candidate. New York is neither Republican nor conservative when it
comes to guns and choice and education and health care and the
economy. So I have a lot of energy for this coming campaign.
</P>
</TEXT>
